  "notes": "Per-hole data taken directly from the RFEG club page (id=521), which embeds hole-by-hole tables for all 10 rated recorridos (Blancas/Amarillas/Azules/Rojas/Naranjas, M and F). Par (4,5,4,4,3,5,3,4,4 / 5,4,3,4,4,3,4,5,4; front 3136m, back 3120m from Blancas) and stroke index match the club's official website hole descriptions exactly; SI is identical across tees/genders on the RFEG card (even SIs front nine, odd back nine). Golfshake yardage totals convert to matching meter totals (yellow 6651yd=6082m, blue 6166yd=5638m, red 5770yd=5276m). Discrepancies: (1) the WHS conversion-table PDF on the club site (dated 25/07/2015) lists older ratings (men Blancas 72.5/138, Amarillas 71.7/136, Azules 69.6/127, Rojas 68.4/132; women Azules 76.0/137, Rojas 73.5/133) — superseded by the current RFEG page values reported here; (2) Amarillas (W) rating 73.3/130 is identical to Rojas (W), which looks like a possible RFEG data-entry duplication given Amarillas is 800m longer — reported as published; (3) club-site prose cites hole 10 as 506m and hole 5 as 168m from yellow vs RFEG 509m/157m (marketing text likely outdated). Naranjas (orange) mapped to color \"gray\" since orange is not an allowed color value."
